Package org.iotivity.service.easysetup.mediator

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CloudProp
    This class contains cloud server properties to be delivered to Enrollee
    CloudPropProvisioningCallback
    This interface class is used as a callback function called after receiving a response of cloud property provisioning result
    CloudPropProvisioningStatus
    This interface facilitates Application to get progress and result of Cloud provisioning process in easy setup
    DeviceProp
    This class contains device properties to be delivered to Enrollee
    DevicePropProvisioningCallback
    This interface class is used as a callback function called after receiving a response of device property provisioning result
    DevicePropProvisioningStatus
    This class indicates a result if a provisionDeviceProperties API succeed or fails
    EasySetup
    This provides an API to instanciate a new RemoteEnrollee object correspondent to Enrollee Device to be setup.
    EnrolleeConf
    This class stores Enrollee's configuration including WiFi and Device configuration including supported WiFi frequency and device name
    EnrolleeStatus
    This class stores Enrollee's status including provisioning status and last error code.
    ESConstants  
    GetConfigurationCallback
    This interface class is used as a callback function called after receiving Enrollee's configuration.
    GetConfigurationStatus
    This class indicates a result if a getConfiguartion API succeed or fails and Enrollee's configuration delivered by a response.
    GetEnrolleeStatus
    This class indicates a result if a getConfiguartion API succeed or fails and Enrollee's configuration delivered by a response.
    GetStatusCallback
    This interface class is used as a callback function called after receiving Enrollee's status.
    RemoteEnrollee
    This class represents Remote Enrollee device instance.
    SecurityProvisioningCallback
    This interface class is used as a callback function called after receiving Security provisioning result
    SecurityProvisioningStatus
    This class indicates a result if a provisionSecurity API succeed or fails and a target Enrollee's device ID
